OL,3,CMother welcomes plans for mandatory
OL,4,Ceye tests for over 70s after son's
OL,5,Cdeath
OL,7,FA woman from Hartley Wintney whose son
OL,8,Fwas killed by an elderly driver with
OL,9,Fpoor eye sight, has welcomed plans for
OL,10,Fcompulsory eye tests for drivers over
OL,11,F70.
OL,13,FPatricia Colquhoun's son died in a
OL,14,Fhead-on collision in 2011. The other
OL,15,Fdriver was an 89-year-old man who was
OL,16,Fblind in one eye.
