OL,3,CMother welcomes plans for mandatory
OL,4,Ceye tests for over 70s after son's
OL,5,Cdeath
OL,7,F"The problem is actually very
OL,8,Fsignificant indeed. We've surveyed our
OL,9,Fmembers, opticians up and down the
OL,10,Fcountry, and over half of them have
OL,11,Fseen somebody in recent months who
OL,12,Fhave failed a sight test, but
OL,13,Fnevertheless the opticians have
OL,14,Fsuspected will continue to drive.
OL,16,F"So this is a very real problem, and
OL,17,Fit's not just a statistical problem.
OL,19,F"We've seen human tragedies.
OL,1,W~s1x0~s1~s hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}   G7/9
